### Key Observations
- **Extreme Salesforce dependency**: At $3.1M (39.5% of spend), Salesforce represents an outsized single-vendor risk.
- **High consolidation opportunity**: 360 long-tail vendors (<$50K each) collectively hold the remaining ~36% of spend — strong candidate pool for rationalization.
- **Real estate & facilities**: TOG UK Properties ($263K), Zagrebtower ($183K), Innovent Spaces ($147K), GPT Space ($133K), and Weking ($144K) suggest multi-site office costs that may be consolidatable.
- **Travel spend duplication**: Two Navan entries (TripActions Inc $358K + Navan Inc $57.9K) suggest possible duplicate/split vendor records totalling ~$416K.